{"type":"finding","iteration":15,"id":"finding:S2-07A:buffered-atomic-writer","title":"Add a debounced dirty writer layer above writeStateAtomic and writeTextAtomic","sourceRefs":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:112-117",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:886-891"],"targetFile":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts","portDifficulty":"med","tag":"quick-win","summary":"Kasper coalesces repeated mutations behind dirty/version/timer state; our atomic helper writes every call immediately, so a buffered wrapper would reduce reducer write bursts without changing atomic replacement semantics."}
{"type":"finding","iteration":15,"id":"finding:S2-07B:immediate-dirty-again-reflush","title":"Use captured version mismatch to reflush immediately after mid-write mutations","sourceRefs":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:894-905",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:939-949"],"targetFile":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts","portDifficulty":"med","tag":"quick-win","summary":"Kasper avoids waiting the normal debounce after a mutation occurs during an async flush; this is the crucial safety layer that keeps coalescing from becoming a larger crash-loss window."}
{"type":"finding","iteration":15,"id":"finding:S2-07C:flush-drain-retry-contract","title":"Expose drain and retry semantics for buffered state writes","sourceRefs":[".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:557-568",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:610-615",".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/156-agent-loops-improved/external/kasper/src/state.ts:920-930"],"targetFile":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts","portDifficulty":"med","tag":"quick-win","summary":"A buffered writer needs explicit flush/drain hooks for shutdown and retries that preserve dirty state after failed writes, otherwise delayed writes can be lost at process boundaries."}
{"type":"observation","iteration":15,"id":"observation:S2-07:target-gap","summary":"Our atomic-state target currently exposes immediate writeStateAtomic/writeTextAtomic only; no dirty flag, debounce timer, in-flight promise, version guard, or drain API exists there.","targetFile":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts","evidence":[".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts:42-43",".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts:58-64"]}
